m various States / UTs. The States / UTs which do not have relevant data for a particular item / category, were excluded while calculating percentages for facilities functioning in Government buildings, manpower vacancies and shortfall etc. Comparative position of infrastructure and manpower for 2014 and 2015 is given in Statements 12-15. </strong></h5><p></p>		\n<iframe src=\"http://13.126.249.59/final_graphs/2.3_avg_villages_covered_by_phc_subcentre__chc_bar.png\"height=\"600\" width=\"800\"></iframe>		\n		<h5><strong>CHCs are being established and maintained by the State government under MNP/BMS programme. As per minimum norms (Box-1), a CHC is required to be manned by four medical specialists i.e. surgeon, physician, gynecologist and pediatrician supported by 21 paramedical and other staff (See Annexure-I for IPHS norms).  It has 30 in-door beds with one OT, X-ray, labour room and laboratory facilities.  It serves as a referral centre for 4 PHCs and also provides facilities for obstetric care and specialist consultations. As on 31st March, 2015, there were 5,396 CHCs functioning in the country. </strong></h5><p></p>','State UT-wise Average Number of Villages Covered by Sub-Centre PHC CHC and Number of sub-Centres Per PHC and Number of PHCs Per CHC ( avg_villages_covered_by_phc_chc )','','inherit','closed','closed','','381-revision-v1','','','2018-03-19 11:31:50','2018-03-19 06:01:50','',381,'http://localhost/wordpress/2018/03/19/381-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(408,1,'2018-03-19 14:53:08','2018-03-19 09:23:08','<h2>Surgeons at Community Health Centres as on 31-03-2017</h2>		\n			<iframe src=\"http://13.126.249.59/final_graphs/surgeon_at_chcs_state_req_post.png\" height=600 width=1000 > </iframe>		\n		<h5><strong>India’s public-health system needs urgent attention and investment – especially in the rural areas, reveals an IndiaSpend analysis. There is an 83% shortage of specialist medical professionals in community health centres, according to the <a href=\"https://nrhm-mis.nic.in/RURAL%20HEALTH%20STATISTICS/(A)RHS%20-%202015/1e-Key_Highlights_from_Rural_Health_Statistics_in_India.pdf\" style=\"color: #008000;\">Rural Health Statistics 2015</a> released by the Ministry of Health &amp; Family Welfare.</strong></h5><p><strong></strong></p>		\n			<iframe src=\"http://13.126.249.59/final_graphs/surgeons_at_chcs_state_in_post.png\" height=600 width=1000> </iframe>		\n		<h5><strong>The CHCs constitute the secondary level of health care and provide specialist care to patients referred from Primary Health Centres, four of which feed into each CHC, serving roughly 80,000 people in tribal, hill or desert areas and 120,000 on the plains.</strong></h5><p><strong></strong></p>		\n<iframe src=\"http://13.126.249.59/final_graphs/surgeons_at_chcs_state_vac_post.png\" height=600 width=1000></iframe>		\n		<h5><strong>An ideal CHC is a 30-bed hospital providing specialist care in medicine, obstetrics and gynaecology, surgery, paediatrics, dental and ayurveda, yoga and naturopathy, unani, siddha and homoeopathy, according to the Indian Public Health Standards <a href=\"http://health.bih.nic.in/docs/guidelines/guidelines-community-health-centres.pdf\" style=\"color: #008000;\">prescribed</a> by the Ministry of Health &amp; Family Welfare in 2012.</strong></h5><strong> </strong><h5><strong>In the 2015 Union Budget, the government cut India’s healthcare budget by 15%, a widely <a href=\"http://www.firstpost.com/business/misplaced-priorities-budget-2015-doesnt-allow-govt-to-take-on-spread-of-diseases-like-swine-flu-2129571.html\" style=\"color: #008000;\">criticised</a> move. The government recently announced it would raise the budget for healthcare, sanitation and child development programmes and sought parliamentary approval, according to a <em>Reuters </em><a href=\"http://in.reuters.com/article/2015/07/31/india-budget-idINKCN0Q51DY20150731\" style=\"color: #008000;\">report</a>.</strong></h5>		\n			<iframe src=\"http://13.126.249.59/final_graphs/surgeons_at_chcs_state_in_post.png\" height=600 width=1000></iframe>		\n			<iframe src=\"http://13.126.249.59/final_graphs/surgeons_at_chcs_state_sanc_post.png\" height=800 width=1000></iframe>','State UT-wise Surgeons at Community Health Centres (CHCs) as on 31-03-2017 ( surgeons_at_chcs )','','inherit','closed','closed','','315-revision-v1','','','2018-03-19 14:53:08','2018-03-19 09:23:08','',315,'http://localhost/wordpress/2018/03/19/315-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(409,1,'2018-03-20 20:08:33','2018-03-20 14:38:33','<h2>Contact form submission from CyberBigAn (http://localhost/wordpress)</h2>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Name:</th>\r\n<td>rahul</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Email:</th>\r\n<td>devendrakumar_r@srmuniv.edu.in</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Subject:</th>\r\n<td>tesingq</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Message:</th>\r\n<td>kjhjkhjkhjk this is tesing of from form og local cyberbigan websirte</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>IP address:</th>\r\n<td>::1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>IP search:</th>\r\n<td>http://whatismyipaddress.com/ip/::1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Came from:</th>\r\n<td>http://localhost/wordpress/test-csv-image/</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Sent from page:</th>\r\n<td>http://localhost/wordpress/</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>','Tuesday, Mar 20, 2018 by \"rahul\"','','private','closed','closed','','tuesday-mar-20-2018-by-rahul','','','2018-03-20 20:08:33','2018-03-20 14:38:33','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/pf_contact/tuesday-mar-20-2018-by-rahul/',0,'pf_contact','',0),(410,1,'2018-03-20 20:10:53','2018-03-20 14:40:53','','','','publish','closed','closed','','410','','','2018-03-20 20:10:53','2018-03-20 14:40:53','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/nf_sub/410/',0,'nf_sub','',0),(411,1,'2018-03-21 03:05:20','2018-03-20 21:35:20','<iframe src=\"http://35.154.9.18:3838\" height=\"500\" width=\"600\"></iframe>','R-Stdio Visulizer','','publish','closed','closed','','r-stdio-visulizer','','','2018-03-21 03:18:49','2018-03-20